        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 8 at 6:42PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Caprock, or 20 miles west of Tatum, moving southwest at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caprock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
